<article>
    <h1>The Na&#xAD;jib tri&#xAD;als</h1>
    <h2>There are five tri&#xAD;als cov&#xAD;er&#xAD;ing a total of 42 crim&#xAD;i&#xAD;nal charges against for&#xAD;mer Malaysian prime min&#xAD;is&#xAD;ter Na&#xAD;jib Razak, mainly over cor&#xAD;rup&#xAD;tion and money laun&#xAD;der&#xAD;ing re&#xAD;lated to 1Malaysia De&#xAD;vel&#xAD;op&#xAD;ment Ber&#xAD;had (1MDB) funds.</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200802/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-02"><time>2020-08-02</time></a>
        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline">Ha&#xAD;zlin Has&#xAD;san</span>
    </section>

    <p>SRC case in­volv­ing RM42 mil­lion (S$13.5 mil­lion)</p>
    <p>Trial con­cluded last Tues­day.</p>
    <p>Na­jib was found guilty of three counts of crim­i­nal breach of trust, three counts of money laun­der­ing and one count of abuse of power over RM42 mil­lion linked to SRC In­ter­na­tional, a for­mer 1MDB sub­sidiary. He was sen­tenced to 12 years in jail and fined RM210 mil­lion. He has been granted a stay of ex­e­cu­tion pend­ing his appeal.</p>
    <p>1MDB case in­volv­ing RM2.28 bil­lion</p>
    <p>Trial be­gan on Aug 28 last year and re­sumes to­mor­row.</p>
    <p>Na­jib faces 21 charges of money laun­der­ing and four charges of abuse of power in con­nec­tion with RM2.28 bil­lion be­lieved to be from state fund 1MDB that was found in his personal bank ac­count.</p>
    <p>1MDB case in­volv­ing RM6.6 bil­lion</p>
    <p>Trial to re­sume.</p>
    <p>Na­jib is jointly charged with for­mer Trea­sury sec­re­tary-gen­eral Mohd Ir­wan Seri­gar Ab­dul­lah with six counts of mis­ap­pro­pri­at­ing RM6.6 bil­lion linked to 1MDB for pay­ment to Abu Dhabi’s In­ter­na­tional Petroleum In­vest­ment Com­pany.</p>
    <p>SRC case in­volv­ing RM27 mil­lion</p>
    <p>Trial post­poned to give way to the 1MDB and au­dit re­port tri­als.</p>
    <p>Na­jib faces three counts of money laun­der­ing re­lated to RM27 mil­lion of SRC In­ter­na­tional funds.</p>
    <p>Tam­per­ing with au­dit re­port</p>
    <p>Trial to re­sume on Aug 10.</p>
    <p>Na­jib and for­mer 1MDB chief ex­ec­u­tive Arul Kanda Kan­dasamy have been charged with tam­per­ing with a 2016 fed­eral au­dit re­port on 1MDB.</p>


</article>

